To run, navigate to the root directory of main.rb in command line and run "ruby main.rb" without quotes.

In order to run this, you need Tk. If you used the one click installer from the Ruby website, then you already have Tk. Otherwise, use "sudo apt-get install libtcltk-ruby" and then proceed with the instructions in the above paragraph.

Currently, this is incredibly buggy and feature free, though hopefully this will change in the near future. Right now, think of this as Computer Science 1 stuff. Elements are hard coded in fixed positions, and there is minimal/no exception handling. Do not expect to use this in a production environment.
